<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" class="border"><tr class="header_bg"><td height="2"><font class="h1font">Tick Tock</B></font></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td><font class="bfont"><font class="bfont"> From: The Founder</font><BR><table><TR><TD><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/freedomcon/buzz.php'>Back to Topics List</A></font></td><td width=40>&nbsp;</td><BR><td><font class="bfont"><A HREF='#postarea'>Jump to Post Area</A></font></td><td width=40>&nbsp;</td><BR><td><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/freedomcon/buzz.php?id=8473'><b>REFRESH THIS TOPIC</b></A></font></td><td width=40>&nbsp;</td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH='100%' border=0 cellpadding=6><tr><td width='4' bgcolor=#EFF1FF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#EFF1FF><font class="h2font"> Name</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' bgcolor=#EFF1FF><font class="h2font"> Comment</td></tr><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Ken B</B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/freedomcon/buzz.php?ignorename=Ken B'>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">Looks like fun--I&#39;m always keen on games to be played with a standard deck of cards. <br><BR><font size=1>11:50 12-20-2006</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#EFF1FF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#EFF1FF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=187">Bane Slader™</a></B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/freedomcon/buzz.php?ignorename=<a href="http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=187">Bane Slader™</a>'>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#EFF1FF' ><font class="bfont">I would give it a try.  Looks pretty good there dude. <br><BR><font size=1>10:27 12-20-2006</font><BR><BR><img src="http://chicago.cubs.mlb.com/chc/images/history/logo_retro_81x81.gif">Let&#39;s play two ... and then go out and have 24!!!</TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=17">Dredlox™</a></B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/freedomcon/buzz.php?ignorename=<a href="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=17">Dredlox™</a>'>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">That is a fun game. I really enjoyed playing it with you and cherry <br><BR><font size=1>00:05 12-20-2006</font><BR><BR>I am not boring. I am not boring at ALL!</TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#EFF1FF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#EFF1FF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/premium/main/mpage.php?member=1">The Founder™</a></B></font><br><font class="afont"> <A HREF='/freedomcon/buzz.php?ignorename=<a href="http://www.decktech.net/premium/main/mpage.php?member=1">The Founder™</a>'>Ignore</A></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#EFF1FF' ><font class="bfont">7 card Tick Tock<br />
<br />
Here is a game loosely based on poker for 3 or more players. Its a ton of fun for people who understand poker hands and want a card game that takes some thought.<br />
<br />
How To Win: Be the first player to accumulate 200 points.<br />
<br />
To Start: Using a regular 52 card deck deal out 7 cards to all players. Afterward flip a card off the top of the deck face up in front of the dealer. This becomes the starting hand. <br />
<br />
Rules: Play goes clockwise starting with the player to the left of the dealer (the dealer should rotate clockwise as well). <br />
<br />
When it is your turn you have two options: <br />
<br />
Play: <br />
1.If there are three or more hands face up on the table, flip all but the last two played hands face down to the center of the table, this location is know as the center of the clock. Rotate the remaining two face up hands to the 12 o&#39;clock and 3 o&#39;clock position relative to the active player. Make sure not to reverse the order of the face up hands.<br />
THEN<br />
2.Play a valid hand to the 6 o&#39;clock position that beats 3 o&#39;clock hand. <br />
OR<br />
3.Using any of the cards from the 3 o&#39;clock hand play two valid hands (to the 3 o&#39;clock and 6 o&#39;clock position) that are progressively better than the 12 o&#39;clock hand.   <br />
<br />
At the end of your turn there should be three valid hands face up on the clock, at the 12, 3, and 6 o&#39;clock position respectively. The 3 o&#39;clock hand (the tick), must beat the 12 o&#39;clock hand AND the 6 o&#39;clock hand (the tock) must beat the 3 o&#39;clock hand.<br />
<br />
The only exception to this is immediately after a deal, or someone wins a clock when the first hand is played. On the first play there will only be one hand face up. Move that hand to the 3 o&#39;clock position and play as normal considering the 12 o&#39;clock hand to have no value.<br />
<br />
Pass: If you can not, or choose not to play any hands this turn you must draw a card from the deck and add it to your hand. Play then continues to the next player.<br />
<br />
A Valid Hand:<br />
A hand consist of 1 to 5 cards where all the cards in the hand play an active part in creating the hand rank. So if I play a 2 of clubs, the hand is valid because the hand is a 2 high. If a play three aces then the hand is three of a kind. I can not play any cards that don&#39;t add to rank directly. So though three aces aces and a king kicker is technically better than three aces by themselves it is not valid because the king does not improve or define the actual rank. The hand is still three of a kind. This prevents someone from playing and Ace high, with 4 scrub cards, or a four of a kind with a kicker etc.<br />
<br />
Suit Ranks: <br />
Spade, Heart, Club, Diamond where Spade is the highest rank and diamond the lowest.<br />
<br />
<br />
A player wins the clock if all players pass back around to that player. Take cards on the clock face up and face down and stack them face down near you. Then play another hand to the table in front of you.<br />
<br />
The round ends when a player wins a clock and any player has no cards in his or her hand. The first person to run out of cards in his or her hand then adds the cards remaining in the deck to his or her count pile along with any cards remaining in any other players hands. <br />
<br />
Count the cards in your count pile. This is your score for this round. Record it. Afterwards collect the cards, shuffle, and start a new round. The first person to 200 wins, if two players break 200 on the same round the one with the highest count wins. <br />
<br />
<br />
Tick Tock (Mental)<br />
<br />
Played the same as 7 card, except ALL cards are dealt out to the players such that each player has the exact same number of cards. Any cards remaining in the deck form the starting hand. When you pass you do not draw a card. The first person to go out only gets the card in the other players hand, as there <br />
are no cards in the deck.<br />
<br />
If there are no cards left in the deck when you complete the deal, the first person plays as normal, not having to beat any hand.<br />
